<subSubSection lastPageId="106" lastPageNumber="363" pageId="105" pageNumber="362" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="105.[794,1422,1808,2008]" lastBlockId="106.[166,794,1297,1848]" lastPageId="106" lastPageNumber="363" pageId="105" pageNumber="362">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[794,928,1808,1832]" pageId="105" pageNumber="362">Description</emphasis>
. Body 
<quantity box="[1014,1101,1809,1832]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" pageId="105" pageNumber="362" unit="mm" value="2.2">2.2 mm</quantity>
long, 0.3 wide mm with 30 chaetigers. Dorsal cirri long, with hyaline vacuoles on most articles (
<figureCitation box="[888,991,1868,1891]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="106.[166,201,988,1009]" captionTargetBox="[166,1443,124,1278]" captionTargetId="figure-8@106.[204,1443,109,1278]" captionTargetPageId="106" captionText="Fig. 89. Syllides spinosus Hartmann-Schröder, 1979 (A) anterior end," pageId="105" pageNumber="362">Fig. 89A</figureCitation>
). Tufts of cilia in front of each anterior eyespot. Ciliary bands on dorsum of each segment (
<figureCitation captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="106.[166,201,988,1009]" captionTargetBox="[166,1443,124,1278]" captionTargetId="figure-8@106.[204,1443,109,1278]" captionTargetPageId="106" captionText="Fig. 89. Syllides spinosus Hartmann-Schröder, 1979 (A) anterior end," pageId="105" pageNumber="362">Fig. 89A</figureCitation>
). Parapodia with about 5 compound chaetae, relatively long blades, bidentate, both teeth distinctly separated, with short spines on margin; blades of 2 medium length 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[166,271,1297,1321]" pageId="106" pageNumber="363">Remarks</emphasis>
. The long, basal spurs on medium-length blades of compound chaetae have not previously been described. This character is considered to be a useful character to distinguish between species in this genus. 
<taxonomicName authority="Perkins, 1981" authorityName="Perkins" authorityYear="1981" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Syllides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="106" pageNumber="363" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="bansei">
<emphasis box="[631,793,1386,1409]" italics="true" pageId="106" pageNumber="363">Syllides bansei</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Perkins, T" box="[166,314,1415,1438]" pageId="106" pageNumber="363" pagination="1080 - 1172" refId="ref67583" refString="Perkins, T. H., 1981. Syllidae (Polychaeta), principally from Florida, with descriptions of a new genus and twenty-one new species. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington 93 (4): 1080 - 1172." type="journal article" year="1981">Perkins, 1981</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, has similar compound chaetae, but the dorsal simple chaetae differ in having a distal hood (
<bibRefCitation author="Perkins, T" box="[633,782,1444,1467]" pageId="106" pageNumber="363" pagination="1080 - 1172" refId="ref67583" refString="Perkins, T. H., 1981. Syllidae (Polychaeta), principally from Florida, with descriptions of a new genus and twenty-one new species. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington 93 (4): 1080 - 1172." type="journal article" year="1981">Perkins, 1981</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authority="Westheide, 1974" authorityName="Westheide" authorityYear="1974" box="[166,573,1473,1497]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Syllides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="106" pageNumber="363" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="edentatus">
<emphasis box="[166,372,1474,1497]" italics="true" pageId="106" pageNumber="363">Syllides edentatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Westheide, W" box="[382,573,1473,1496]" pageId="106" pageNumber="363" pagination="195 - 338" refId="ref68411" refString="Westheide, W., 1974. Interstitielle Fauna von Galapagos. XI. Pisionidae, Pilargidae, Syllidae. Mikrofauna Meeresbodens 44: 195 - 338." type="journal article" year="1974">Westheide, 1974</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, also has a similar arrangement of chaetae, but the pair of the medium size chaetae have several long spines instead of a single basal spur as occurs in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hartmann-Schroder" authorityYear="1979" box="[357,541,1562,1585]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Syllides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="106" pageNumber="363" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="spinosus">
<emphasis box="[357,541,1562,1585]" italics="true" pageId="106" pageNumber="363">Syllides spinosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Westheide, W" box="[556,741,1561,1584]" pageId="106" pageNumber="363" pagination="195 - 338" refId="ref68411" refString="Westheide, W., 1974. Interstitielle Fauna von Galapagos. XI. Pisionidae, Pilargidae, Syllidae. Mikrofauna Meeresbodens 44: 195 - 338." type="journal article" year="1974">Westheide, 1974</bibRefCitation>
; San Martín, 2003). 
<taxonomicName authority="Banse, 1972" authorityName="Banse" authorityYear="1972" box="[333,672,1591,1614]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Syllides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="106" pageNumber="363" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="benedicti">
<emphasis box="[333,525,1591,1614]" italics="true" pageId="106" pageNumber="363">Syllides benedicti</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Banse, K" box="[534,672,1591,1614]" pageId="106" pageNumber="363" pagination="1469 - 1481" refId="ref63804" refString="Banse, K., 1972. A new species, and additions to the descriptions of six other species of Syllides Orsted (Syllidae: Polychaeta). Journal of Fisheries Research Board of Canada 28 (10): 1469 - 1481." type="journal article" year="1972">Banse, 1972</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, also has a single long basal spur on the pair of medium-length bladed chaetae, but the dorsal simple chaetae are distally rounded, with some spines present in addition to the spines on margin (
<bibRefCitation author="Banse, K" box="[174,312,1708,1731]" pageId="106" pageNumber="363" pagination="1469 - 1481" refId="ref63804" refString="Banse, K., 1972. A new species, and additions to the descriptions of six other species of Syllides Orsted (Syllidae: Polychaeta). Journal of Fisheries Research Board of Canada 28 (10): 1469 - 1481." type="journal article" year="1972">Banse, 1972</bibRefCitation>
). For a discussion of the differences between the stem species 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ehlers" authorityYear="1897" box="[378,543,1738,1761]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Syllides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="106" pageNumber="363" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="articulosus">
<emphasis box="[378,543,1738,1761]" italics="true" pageId="106" pageNumber="363">S. articulosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hartmann-Schroder" authorityYear="1979" box="[610,744,1738,1761]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Syllides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="106" pageNumber="363" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="spinosus">
<emphasis box="[610,744,1738,1761]" italics="true" pageId="106" pageNumber="363">S. spinosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
see 
<bibRefCitation author="Hartmann-Schroder, G" box="[166,444,1767,1790]" pageId="106" pageNumber="363" pagination="75 - 218" refId="ref65657" refString="Hartmann-Schroder, G., 1979. Teil 2. Die Polychaeten der tropischen Nordwestkuste Australiens (zwischen Port Samson in Norden und Port Hedland in Suden). Mitteilungen aus dem Hamburgischen Zoologischen Museum und Institut 76: 75 - 218." type="journal article" year="1979">Hartmann-Schröder, 1979</bibRefCitation>
; furthermore, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ehlers" authorityYear="1897" box="[591,734,1767,1790]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Syllides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="106" pageNumber="363" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="articulosus">
<emphasis box="[591,734,1767,1790]" italics="true" pageId="106" pageNumber="363">S. articulosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lacks long basal spurs on any blade (
<bibRefCitation author="Somaschini, A" pageId="106" pageNumber="363" pagination="267 - 271" refId="ref68209" refString="Somaschini, A., &amp; G. San Martin, 1997. First report of Syllides articulosus (Polychaeta: Syllidae: Eusyllinae) for the Mediterranean Sea. Vie Milieu 47 (3): 267 - 271." type="journal article" year="1997">Somaschini &amp; San Martín, 1997</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
